{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The EU has also acknowledged their importance in XR and to facilitate other rights.",
    "\"Online privacy and safety\" is a crucial pillar of the EU \"Digital Decade\" initiative (European Commission, 2021), and both are included in the European Declaration on Digital Rights and Principles for the Digital Decade.",
    "foot_1 These high-level goals manifest in a European Parliamentary Research Service (EPRS) report on the \"metaverse\" (Madiega et al., 2022), which highlights the importance of physical and mental health issues and data privacy, while the July 2023 \"EU initiative on Web 4.0 and virtual worlds\" recognizes challenges to \"personal data and privacy,\" cybercrime, and cyber violence (European Commission, 2023).",
    "Third, although we provide recommendations to EU policymakers, our map of safety and privacy risks and some of our recommendations may also apply to other jurisdictions.",
    "Because IXR is a global and pan-jurisdictional phenomenon, we hope this article will contribute to a more extensive discussion of how safety and privacy protections can be harmonized in other contexts."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
